From: Agriya Khetarpal <74401230+agriyakhetarpal@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 17 May 2026 21:09:09 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] Add WASM-compatible sync() for Pyodide

Pyodide uses WebLoop as its asyncio event loop, which registers itself as
the running loop at process start. zarr's sync() previously spawned a
background I/O thread with its own event loop, which is incompatible with
WASM's single-threaded model and causes RuntimeErrors when called from the
browser.

On WASM, sync() now delegates to the already-running WebLoop via
run_until_complete(). If JSPI is not available the loop returns the
coroutine as a Future instead of awaiting it; we detect this and raise a
descriptive RuntimeError pointing users to the async API or a
JSPI-enabled environment. _get_loop() likewise raises immediately on WASM
since the background thread and its loop are never created there.

Upstream reference: https://github.com/zarr-developers/zarr-python/pull/1903
